# TanStack Query Key Factory Convention

- Keep one feature-local query key factory per feature query module (for example, `src/hooks/queries/users/queryKeys.ts`).
- Export a single `queryKeys` object from each factory file; keep it as the only source of truth for query keys.
- Define keys as readonly tuple-returning helpers (for example, `detail: (id: string) => ["users", "detail", id] as const`).
- Never write inline keys in hooks or components (for example, avoid `queryKey: ["users", id]`).
- Use the factory in every `useQuery`, `useInfiniteQuery`, cache invalidation, and optimistic update path (`getQueryData`, `setQueryData`, `invalidateQueries`).
- Keep key segments stable and explicit (`entity`, `scope`, `params`) to avoid accidental cache collisions.
